15/04/2011
BELGRADE, Serbia -- The organised crime prosecutor's office announced on Thursday (April 14th) that three people have been arrested for smuggling 990kg of cocaine, part of a larger shipment of more than two tonnes of cocaine seized in Uruguay in October 2009. 
Darko Saric and his group are suspected of smuggling the drugs. 
He remains on the run. 
(Beta, B92, Tanjug - 14/04/11)
